I have followed the documentation entitled "cantera155-build-
win32.pdf" to the letter. I installed everything according to the 
documentation except Matlab.

When I tried to build, (using Visual C++ .NET 2003), it gave me "119 
Build error tasks shown" in the Task List tab. In the Output tab, it 
reads at the end: 16 succeeded, 2 failed and 1 skipped (I presume 
SetupCantera was skipped). 

I have no idea why it fails to compile completely.

As far as I can tell, it's having problems with ck2cti, tpx.lib and 
clib.lib.  Attached are some of the error messages.

Also when I tried to build "SetupCantera," it produces an error 
because it can't find ck2cti.exe.
